<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: POINT MUGU; 
</P>
<P>
HORNET JETS BEGIN SERIES OF EXERCISES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An attack squadron of F/A-18 Hornet jets will practicing takeoffs and landings 
for two weeks beginning today at the Pacific Missile Test Center in Point Mugu. 
</P>
<P>
Today's half-hour practices are scheduled at 11 a.m. and 6:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The exercises are planned at least three days a week until Aug. 3. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Thursday, the sessions will begin at 11 a.m. and continue throughout 
the day until 8:30 p.m. The times may change slightly due to operational needs 
or weather conditions. 
</P>
<P>
In the past, the annual exercise has prompted telephone calls from residents 
who wonder if the increased activity on the base is a cause for concern, Navy 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
A maximum of four jets will be in the air at one time, practicing landings in 
preparation for their annual two-week exercise period next month. HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
