<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
PHOTOS OF 4 SUPERVISORS STILL MISSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The county is on a picture hunt, seeking photographs of four former members of 
the Board of Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
If found, the missing photos will complete a "Supervisors Picture Project" that 
was started several years ago and now includes about 50 former and present 
members of the board -- all but four who have served since the county was 
founded in 1873. 
</P>
<P>
The missing supervisors are: 
</P>
<P>
* H.L. Atwood, who served four years starting Jan. 1, 1877. 
</P>
<P>
* Robert Ayers, who served four years starting Jan. 1, 1885. 
</P>
<P>
* Charles C. Perkins, who served four years starting Jan. 1, 1915. 
</P>
<P>
* Edward S. Pierce, who served four years starting Jan. 1, 1949. 
</P>
<P>
"We would like to ask your board and members of the public to put out the word" 
that the pictures are needed to complete the collection, Susan Van Abel, the 
county's principal administrative analyst, told board members Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
"The pictures, which are truly amazing, along with a map of the county, will 
depict the historical perspective and hairstyles of the county," Van Abel said. 
</P>
<P>
With or without the missing photographs, the collection will go on display 
starting next month on the fourth floor of the Hall of Administration in the 
County Government Center in Ventura. JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</TEXT>
