<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT WIRE BURNS 2 THEFT SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two San Fernando Valley men were burned, one seriously, when they tried to 
steal copper wire from a live electric transformer in Santa Clarita on Tuesday, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
Steve A. Lambardo, 25, of Sylmar and James A. Lorner, 24, of Northridge were 
injured about 4 p.m. when they attempted to remove copper wire from the 
Southern California Edison consumer substation on Bouquet Canyon Road, said Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Lt. Tim Peters. 
</P>
<P>
Lorner was in serious condition at Henry Mayo Newhall Hospital on Tuesday night 
as doctors searched for space at an area burn center, Peters said. Lambardo was 
treated at the hospital and released to police. 
</P>
<P>
The two men and a third person authorities said was involved, Shelia Panzer, 
24, of Northridge, were arrested on charges of attempted grand theft, felony 
vandalism and trespassing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
