<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mark and Brian and the Diceman: Andrew Dice Clay took to the airwaves Tuesday 
morning as a guest on KLOS 95.5 FM's Mark and Brian Show. 
</P>
<P>
The show's producer, Nicole Sandler, said that Clay took unscreened listener 
calls from 8 to 10 a.m. in his only local radio appearance. "It's the first 
time he's ever taken phone calls like that," said Sandler. "He really dropped 
the Diceman act and talked to people." She said he explained that what he does 
is only an act. "Some people were hostile at the beginning, but to my surprise, 
there wasn't one person who went away angry," said Sandler. Clay fielded 25 
calls. BETH KLEID 
