<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SEARCH CONTINUES FOR 2 ABOARD CAPSIZED 
VESSEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men who were rescued from the ocean after clinging to an ice chest for 18 
hours remained in serious condition Tuesday, while a Coast Guard vessel 
continued to search for two other men who were aboard the 14-foot motorboat 
when it capsized. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel Echeverria, 22, was moved out of intensive care at UCLA Medical Center 
Tuesday afternoon, hospital sources said, but his companion, Jorge Hernandez, 
28, remains in the intensive care unit. 
</P>
<P>
Echeverria and Hernandez were rescued about 2 p.m. Monday by Los Angeles County 
lifeguards after clinging to an ice chest since 8 p.m. Sunday -- a total of 18 
hours in 65-degree water. Echeverria, Hernandez and two others left Marina del 
Rey in a yellow, 14-foot motorboat about 11 a.m. Sunday for a fishing 
expedition off Malibu. But about 8 p.m., the boat struck a submerged object, 
and the men were tossed into the sea. 
</P>
