</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles City Council on Tuesday voted to file a lawsuit to recover 
$48,250 in government rent subsidies that Bishop H. H. Brookins improperly 
collected from the city. 
</P>
<P>
The money paid to Brookins is owed because the bishop concealed his ownership 
in a Southwest Los Angeles building to receive $339,000 in federal loans to 
renovate the building, a city investigation found. 
</P>
