<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John McEnroe, making his first tournament appearance since an opening-round 
loss at Wimbledon, defeated Paul Chamberlin, 6-2, 6-3, in a second-round match 
of the Sovran Bank Classic at Washington, D.C. 
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded McEnroe did not face a break point until the final game of the 
match and he broke Chamberlin in the sixth game of each set. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt I played pretty well," McEnroe said. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm eager to try to play my best, my absolute best. I feel my game coming 
along, but it takes time." 
</P>
<P>
Said Chamberlain: "We both played bad. I think (McEnroe) needs to do more with 
his court preparation and focus back on his game." 
</P>
<P>
McEnroe's last tournament victory came against Brad Gilbert March 5, 1989, in 
the WCT finals at Dallas. 
</P>
<P>
In other matches, defending champion Tim Mayotte scored a 6-2, 6-1 victory over 
India's Ramesh Krishnan. Second-seeded Brad Gilbert advanced to the third round 
with a 6-1, 7-5 decision over Eliot Teltscher. 
</P>
