<HEADLINE>
<P>
CZECH EMBASSY STANDOFF IN HAVANA ENDS BUT OTHER CUBANS SEEK ASYLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HAVANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fresh group of Cubans sought political asylum at other foreign embassies in 
Havana on Tuesday only hours after a weeklong standoff at the Czechoslovak 
Embassy ended with the surrender of 12 refugees. 
</P>
<P>
Four young Cubans climbed onto the roof of the Italian ambassador's residence 
Tuesday and asked for political asylum, an Italian Embassy spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Cuban police seized and dragged away a Cuban who tried to enter the 
U.S. Interests Section. The section protested to Cuban authorities about the 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
In another development, a family of four Cubans pushed their way into the 
consular section of the Spanish Embassy and demanded visas, diplomatic sources 
said, but they were persuaded to leave and apply for their visas normally. The 
couple and two children already had valid Cuban passports and authorization to 
leave the country. Three Cubans are being sheltered at the embassy. 
</P>
<P>
The new incidents came a day after 12 Cuban refugees surrendered 
unconditionally and left the Czechoslovak Embassy after fighting among 
themselves and holding five Czechoslovak diplomats hostage for more than five 
hours. 
</P>
<P>
Five Cubans are occupying the house of a Czechoslovak diplomat but have been 
refused diplomatic protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
