PEOPLE: MCA APPOINTS HEAD OF BLACK MUSIC DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ernie Singleton, a former senior vice president at Warner Bros. Records, has 
been named president of the black music division at MCA Records. 
</P>
<P>
In his new post, Singleton, 40, will oversee a staff of about 40 employees, 
mostly based at MCA headquarters in Universal City. 
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Singleton, a veteran of the music business who has worked 
with artists such as Quincy Jones, Prince, Bobby Brown and Patti LaBelle, had 
been under negotiation since the beginning of this year. He assumes a post last 
held by Jheryl Busby, now president of Motown Records. 
</P>
