<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
MAN, 26, ARRESTED IN TOT'S BEATING DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Huntington Beach man was arrested Tuesday in connection with last week's 
fatal beating of his girlfriend's 14-month-old daughter, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Wayne Ichija Yoshisato, 26, was arrested at an undisclosed residence in San 
Diego County at 11 a.m. on suspicion of murder. 
</P>
<P>
He is expected to be charged with first-degree murder with special 
circumstances, child abuse and two counts of rape with a foreign object, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach Police Lt. Ed McErlain said investigators focused on Yoshisato 
after interviewing him and others after Felicia Lynn Grunbaum died of massive 
head injuries on July 10. 
</P>
<P>
The child was beaten to death at a house in the 8800 block of Anthony Drive, 
where she lived with her mother, Pepper Ann Grunbaum, 19, and Yoshisato, 
McErlain said. 
</P>
<P>
McErlain declined to elaborate on the circumstances of the murder or on whether 
the child had been abused on prior occasions. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation is continuing, and Yshisato is being held without bail at the 
city jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
