<P>
COUNCIL ALLOCATES FUNDS FOR SENIORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA MASCARO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council agreed Tuesday night to earmark $85,000 on services for 
seniors. 
</P>
<P>
In-home care will receive $35,000 through various agencies. The council also 
indicated that they plan to allocate $50,000 for transportation for seniors. 
The city is still looking for an agency to provide that transportation, because 
none of the applicants qualified. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the council allocated $30,000 for shelter space, $28,500 for youth 
crime prevention and $15,000 for health care services. 
</P>
<P>
Community organizations such as Independencia, Feedback Foundation, YMCA, 
Anaheim Interfaith Shelter, Covering Wings, RSVP, and the Boys and Girls Club 
were among the 13 recipients of funds. LISA MASCARO 
