<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE GET 6.25% RAISE, BENEFITS HIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The police association and the city have reached a two-year agreement on police 
salaries, giving all officers a 6.25% raise and an increase in benefits. 
</P>
<P>
Also, the city agreed to grant a 5% salary increase next July. 
</P>
<P>
The salary range for a senior police officer now starts out at $3,197 a month, 
topping out at $3,886 per month, said Personnel Director Steve Hayman. 
</P>
<P>
The total package will cost the city $543,000. 
</P>
<P>
Meetings between the city personnel department and the Costa Mesa Police Assn. 
resulted in a .75% increase in medical benefits and an agreement to study 
alternative work weeks, in which officers would be given the opportunity to 
work varying shifts. 
</P>
<P>
"Quite frankly, the city's interest in this study is to find out what will 
advance the service levels and productivity out of the work force," Hayman 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
