<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ropak Corp.: The Fullerton maker of plastic packaging and handling products 
said second-quarter net income rose to $1.1 million, a 70% gain from the 
$644,000 posted for the year-earlier period. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue increased 3% to $28.3 million from $27.5 million. For the year's first 
half, Ropak earned $1.3 million, up 44% from $875,000 in the year-earlier 
period. Revenue rose to $49.1 million from $48.5 million. William H. Roper, 
chairman and chief executive, attributed the company's increased earnings to 
improvements in production efficiency and improved profit margins. 
</P>
</TEXT>
